Moron.

234
00:17:40,492 --> 00:17:42,960
This trooper is going to make
the run with that phone.

235
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:46,520
- What's your name, Officer?
- Steven Cardy, but I go by Stevie, mostly.

236
00:17:46,665 --> 00:17:48,292
- How old are you?
- I'm 22, sir.

237
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,494
You're the high-school quarterback that
joined the troopers for excitement?

238
00:17:51,603 --> 00:17:53,696
- How do you know that?
- You have that look.

239
00:17:56,108 --> 00:17:58,576
- Enjoying it so far?
- Yes, sir. I am.

240
00:17:59,778 --> 00:18:02,110
I'm sorry, sir. I mean, it's a terrible situation.

241
00:18:02,214 --> 00:18:04,876
- I'm happy to help as much as I can.
- I know what you mean.

242
00:18:04,983 --> 00:18:06,644
I don't want any heroics today.

243
00:18:07,286 --> 00:18:09,220
You see that pen out there?

244
00:18:09,321 --> 00:18:11,551
I want you to move up there
and you pitch this...

245
00:18:11,657 --> 00:18:15,093
as far as you can towards the front door
of that slaughterhouse.

246
00:18:15,194 --> 00:18:16,718
What if I hit the building with it?

247
00:18:16,829 --> 00:18:18,729
It's a special phone and the bag is padded.

248
00:18:18,831 --> 00:18:22,392
If you hit the building from there,
you ought to give up law enforcement...

249
00:18:22,501 --> 00:18:23,832
and try out for the Jets.

250
00:18:24,036 --> 00:18:25,469
Yes, sir. Okay.

251
00:18:26,171 --> 00:18:28,196
<i>This is Agent Potter again.</i>

252
00:18:28,707 --> 00:18:32,575
<i>One of my men is going to throw this phone
as close as he can.</i>

253
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:36,214
<i>This is not a trick.
It is simply a cellular phone.</i>

254
00:18:38,484 --> 00:18:40,452
<i>Will you let our man approach?</i>

255
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:46,157
You can go.

256
00:18:46,558 --> 00:18:49,823
- Are you sure that means yes?
- They would have said no with a bullet.

257
00:18:49,928 --> 00:18:51,486
- Go on. Keep low.
- Yes, sir.

258
00:19:18,323 --> 00:19:19,449
What the hell is he doing?

259
00:19:19,558 --> 00:19:22,322
I don't know, sir.
Maybe he wants to get closer.

260
00:19:24,630 --> 00:19:27,656
<i>That's far enough, Stevie.
Throw it from there.</i>

261
00:20:32,064 --> 00:20:35,227
Mark down, first contact with the hostage.

262
00:20:35,467 --> 00:20:37,594
Content? What's the communication?

263
00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:41,298
I don't know. Where's the interpreter?

264
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,970
- Christ!
- They're on their way.

265
00:20:49,047 --> 00:20:51,174
Set up a video camera
with a telephoto lens...

266
00:20:51,283 --> 00:20:53,308
and keep it focused
on that upstairs window.

267
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:54,578
Right.

268
00:21:00,792 --> 00:21:02,919
<i>- Yeah.
- Theodore Handy?</i>

269
00:21:04,396 --> 00:21:07,160
- Yeah!
- This is John Potter, FBI.

270
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:10,261
I'd like to talk to you, Ted.
Can I call you Ted?

271
00:21:10,369 --> 00:21:12,200
Well, you got us surrounded...

272
00:21:12,304 --> 00:21:14,932
you got a lot of goons
up there in the trees with guns...

273
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:17,873
you can pretty much call me
whatever you want to.

274
00:21:18,343 --> 00:21:20,971
Ted, this is a real tense situation.

275
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:24,344
<i>No, I'm not tense, I'm not tense at all.
In fact, I'm really relaxed...</i>

276
00:21:24,850 --> 00:21:27,512
'cause I'm getting ready to shoot
one of these little kids.

277
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:29,917
Ted, I don't think you want to kill anybody.

278
00:21:30,088 --> 00:21:32,579
<i>- Do you go by Jack?
- John, actually.</i>

279
00:21:32,691 --> 00:21:34,556
Okay, Jack, now what makes you think...

280
00:21:34,660 --> 00:21:37,060
that I'm not going to shoot myself
one of these kids?

281
00:21:37,162 --> 00:21:38,561
'Cause if you do that...

282
00:21:38,664 --> 00:21:41,064
I have to conclude
that you plan to kill all of them.

283
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:42,997
That's when we come in and take you out.

284
00:21:43,101 --> 00:21:46,434
<i>Bullshit! That's bullshit.
There's no way you're going to take...</i>

285
00:21:46,538 --> 00:21:49,029
<i>a chance at coming in here
and shooting one of these kids.</i>

286
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:53,373
I'm asking you not to kill anyone, Ted.
Can I have your word on that?

287
00:21:54,112 --> 00:21:57,172
Well, I don't know, Jack.
Should I or shouldn't I?

288
00:21:57,683 --> 00:22:00,914
<i>Like, should I or shouldn't I?
You know how that happens sometimes...</i>

289
00:22:01,019 --> 00:22:03,817
you just can't make up your fucking mind?

290
00:22:08,226 --> 00:22:12,094
Mr. Potter, I'm Constance Stanley
from Laurent Clerc school.

291
00:22:12,197 --> 00:22:14,563
We've been anxious for you to get here.

292
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,589
How are they?

293
00:22:16,702 --> 00:22:18,863
They're all still alive, as far as we know.

294
00:22:19,905 --> 00:22:22,203
- You brought the profiles?
- Yes.

295
00:22:23,408 --> 00:22:25,308
Here, please sit down.

296
00:22:27,412 --> 00:22:31,041
- The young teacher?
- Melanie Charrol.

297
00:22:31,450 --> 00:22:34,283
She signed something to me
from the window.

298
00:22:40,559 --> 00:22:44,359
I'm sorry, it's not funny. It's just that
you're making the sign for drink.

299
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:46,087
Could it have been this?

300
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:48,792
- That's it.
- That's the sign for help.

301
00:22:50,669 --> 00:22:52,728
- That makes sense, she wants help.
- Right.

302
00:22:52,838 --> 00:22:56,035
But if you're doing it correctly,
then she wasn't saying, "You help. "

303
00:22:56,141 --> 00:22:58,132
She was saying, "Help you. "

304
00:22:58,243 --> 00:23:01,337
- Help me?
- Yes. Well, I mean, I can't be sure.

305
00:23:03,014 --> 00:23:07,110
I don't understand her wanting to help me,
I can understand her wanting help.

306
00:23:08,353 --> 00:23:10,821
I can even understand her wanting a drink.

307
00:23:11,356 --> 00:23:13,654
When this is over,
I'll buy her a double martini.

308
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:17,092
- How're doing? How's everybody doing?
- God, what are you doing now?

309
00:23:17,195 --> 00:23:18,822
I sure hope nobody smokes.

310
00:23:20,265 --> 00:23:23,063
I chew, but I gave up smoking years ago.

311
00:23:24,469 --> 00:23:25,766
<i>- Yeah.
- Jack, how you doing?</i>

312
00:23:25,871 --> 00:23:27,600
Listen, I want to introduce you...

313
00:23:27,706 --> 00:23:29,731
<i>to Donna, she's the bus driver.</i>

314
00:23:29,841 --> 00:23:33,902
Yeah, here, say hi, and then tell him
exactly what I'm doing. Go.

315
00:23:34,946 --> 00:23:36,971
He's sprinkling gasoline...

316
00:23:37,082 --> 00:23:39,880
<i>- all over the room.
- How are the children?</i>

317
00:23:40,385 --> 00:23:42,717
<i>They're fine, except for Beverly.</i>

318
00:23:42,821 --> 00:23:44,118
<i>She has asthma...</i>

319
00:23:44,222 --> 00:23:48,181
- and these fumes aren't going to help...
- Let's go, down the stairs, honey.

320
00:23:48,293 --> 00:23:50,591
Tell them exactly what I'm doing now.
Don't miss a beat.

321
00:23:50,695 --> 00:23:53,493
He's sprinkling gasoline
all the way down the stairs.

322
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:54,656
Keep going, honey.

323
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:57,064
<i>Turn to your right,
all the way down to the bottom.</i>

324
00:23:57,169 --> 00:24:00,138
<i>We're going down.
We're on the second floor.</i>

325
00:24:00,238 --> 00:24:01,728
Head's up, Shep!

326
00:24:03,742 --> 00:24:06,006
Baby! What's that there?

327
00:24:07,779 --> 00:24:09,246
- It's a lantern.
- Tell him.

328
00:24:09,347 --> 00:24:10,871
- He's pointing to a lantern.
- Right.

329
00:24:10,982 --> 00:24:13,507
What would happen if that lantern fell over?

330
00:24:13,752 --> 00:24:16,550
<i>- The third floor would go up in flames.
- Good. Stand right there.</i>

331
00:24:16,655 --> 00:24:18,782
Jack, did you hear that?
Do you get the picture?

332
00:24:18,890 --> 00:24:20,323
We get the picture.

333
00:24:20,425 --> 00:24:23,656
Good, hang on a sec, Jack.
I'll be with you in a second here.

334
00:24:23,762 --> 00:24:25,093
Hey, Sonny.

335
00:24:25,197 --> 00:24:28,257
This here's gonna be your spot,
it's gonna be your post, okay?

336
00:24:28,366 --> 00:24:29,890
I want you right there on the steps.

337
00:24:30,001 --> 00:24:34,062
In case any of those little canary birds
come down here, toss that lantern over.

338
00:24:34,172 --> 00:24:37,869
If someone tries to shoot or
come in the windows, toss the lantern over.

339
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:42,041
Come on, man, that means
I'm stuck here with them up there...

340
00:24:42,147 --> 00:24:44,843
I'm here alone and you guys are downstairs.

341
00:24:45,283 --> 00:24:47,683
- You got a problem with that?
- No.

342
00:24:49,354 --> 00:24:51,151
Let's go, walk.

343
00:24:53,558 --> 00:24:55,082
Jack, you're still there?

344
00:24:55,193 --> 00:24:57,718
<i>Listen, this here is something neat...</i>

345
00:24:57,829 --> 00:24:59,854
<i>- I'm going to let the bus driver go.
- No.</i>

346
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:04,268
- Wait! Let one of the children go, please.
- No. This is your lucky day, darling.

347
00:25:04,603 --> 00:25:08,266
<i>- Great, Ted. I appreciate that.
- I want to let you know that I'm not all bad.</i>

348
00:25:08,373 --> 00:25:10,739
- Check you later.
- How are you going to talk to them?

349
00:25:10,842 --> 00:25:13,504
Melanie and me is going
to get along just fine, darling.

350
00:25:27,259 --> 00:25:30,422
- Go on out there and meet her, Stevie.
- Yes, sir.

351
00:25:42,807 --> 00:25:46,641
Why would he tell us about
the gasoline and then send her out?

352
00:25:49,681 --> 00:25:52,343
John, don't try it. John!

353
00:25:52,884 --> 00:25:55,580
Get down!

354
00:26:00,525 --> 00:26:01,685
Don't run.

355
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:05,127
No, stay down! Get on the ground!

356
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:23,538
Downlink!

357
00:26:28,653 --> 00:26:30,621
- Potter.
- Jack.

358
00:26:31,256 --> 00:26:35,420
There's one thing you got to understand
about me. I don't care about that bus driver.

359
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:38,290
I don't care about the teacher
or these little boys and girls.

360
00:26:38,396 --> 00:26:41,627
These are all just like
little birds I use to shoot back home...

361
00:26:41,733 --> 00:26:44,827
<i>off my front porch.
Now, you can go pick her up.</i>

362
00:26:44,936 --> 00:26:47,962
I'm not going to shoot you.
You just better give me what I want.

363
00:26:48,206 --> 00:26:51,573
- And what do you want?
- Get back to you on that.

364
00:27:37,789 --> 00:27:39,620
Should we move some of our people closer?

365
00:27:39,724 --> 00:27:41,817
No, we do nothing. Nothing.

366
00:27:42,961 --> 00:27:44,451
It's his move.

367
00:29:01,806 --> 00:29:02,966
Downlink.

368
00:29:07,045 --> 00:29:08,569
- Yeah.
- Yeah, Jack.

369
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:11,148
Listen, I've had a chance
to think it over. Did you?

370
00:29:11,249 --> 00:29:14,514
Yes, I did. But we have to get
one thing straight.

371
00:29:14,619 --> 00:29:18,146
I'm the only man in this universe
that can get you out of there alive.

372
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:21,453
There's nobody else.
I'm the one to reckon with, Ted.

373
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:24,357
That may be, but in the meantime,
you know, we're starving.

374
00:29:24,462 --> 00:29:27,829
My buddy is starting to disappear
before my eyes. You should see him.

375
00:29:27,932 --> 00:29:29,991
You know what we never get in prison?

376
00:29:30,101 --> 00:29:33,161
<i>- Pizza. Ain't that right, Shep?
- Where's the nearest pizza place?</i>

377
00:29:33,671 --> 00:29:36,299
There's one over at Beaumont,
10-15 minutes.

378
00:29:36,541 --> 00:29:38,805
It'll take about an hour, Ted. What else?

379
00:29:38,977 --> 00:29:41,844
<i>- A helicopter, real big one.
- I'll work on it. What else?</i>

380
00:29:42,647 --> 00:29:46,105
<i>Let me see. I need 100 rounds
of 12-gauge double aught.</i>

381
00:29:46,284 --> 00:29:48,218
I guess you know I can't do that.

382
00:29:48,620 --> 00:29:51,817
<i>- Even if I was to give you a girl, Jack?
- Sorry.</i>

383
00:29:52,190 --> 00:29:54,249
<i>Weapons and ammo are deal breakers.</i>

384
00:29:54,359 --> 00:29:57,021
Yeah, I hear you, Jack.

385
00:29:57,128 --> 00:30:00,154
<i>But if we were to do some horse-trading,
which one would you want?</i>

386
00:30:00,265 --> 00:30:03,098
<i>Would you want anyone in particular?
How about the teacher?</i>

387
00:30:03,201 --> 00:30:05,567
<i>I mean, she's so fucking sexy, isn't she?</i>

388
00:30:05,670 --> 00:30:08,104
<i>She looks good, she smells good.</i>

389
00:30:08,206 --> 00:30:09,988
Hell, if I wasn't so devoted to Priscilla,
I'd take a stab at her myself.

390
00:30:10,023 --> 00:30:11,771
Hell, if I wasn't so devoted to Priscilla,
I'd take a stab at her myself.

391
00:30:11,876 --> 00:30:14,936
<i>- Yeah, one of the girls has asthma.
- Yeah, no shit.</i>

392
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:18,813
For a deaf kid, she sure makes a racket,
I'll tell you that.

393
00:30:19,417 --> 00:30:21,180
<i>That means she's coming out, Ted?</i>

394
00:30:21,286 --> 00:30:24,744
No, Jack. What it means is I'm going
to shoot her in exactly two minutes...

395
00:30:24,856 --> 00:30:27,552
if I don't get that ammo. Start timing.

396
00:30:30,595 --> 00:30:31,619
Shit.

397
00:30:32,263 --> 00:30:34,857
Get up. Sit down, lady. Sit down.

398
00:30:35,033 --> 00:30:37,763
Get down on your ass, get your ass down.

399
00:30:39,504 --> 00:30:41,597
- Jesus!
- He's at the window.

400
00:30:46,911 --> 00:30:49,812
- Call it out, Toby.
- One minute, 30 seconds.

401
00:30:53,051 --> 00:30:55,679
Do something.
Tell him you'll give him the shells.

402
00:30:55,787 --> 00:30:58,085
- No.
- He's going to shoot her.

403
00:30:58,356 --> 00:31:00,221
I don't think he will.

404
00:31:03,695 --> 00:31:05,492
- Sonny!
- Yeah.

405
00:31:05,597 --> 00:31:08,327
- Get up here now!
- Coming! What?

406
00:31:08,433 --> 00:31:10,901
Get this one, take her down to the post
and tie her up.

407
00:31:11,002 --> 00:31:13,527
- Take her down right now, hurry up.
- Come on. Move.

408
00:31:20,345 --> 00:31:21,710
One minute.

409
00:31:23,348 --> 00:31:26,943
- Send them some blanks.
- Maybe some ammo that'll jam the guns?

410
00:31:27,051 --> 00:31:28,075
No.

411
00:31:28,987 --> 00:31:33,390
- Okay, that's it. I'm going out there.
- Hold it, Lenny. You're not going anywhere.

412
00:31:34,192 --> 00:31:36,092
He's going to kill her in cold blood.

413
00:31:36,194 --> 00:31:37,889
- He's not.
- Thirty seconds.

414
00:31:37,996 --> 00:31:40,226
How the hell do you know that?

415
00:31:49,807 --> 00:31:51,331
Twenty seconds.

416
00:31:54,545 --> 00:31:56,137
Fifteen seconds.

417
00:31:59,784 --> 00:32:02,252
Ten seconds, nine, eight...

418
00:32:06,024 --> 00:32:07,685
Three, two.

419
00:32:09,494 --> 00:32:12,156
Zero, that's two minutes.

420
00:32:15,333 --> 00:32:17,358
Two minutes, five seconds.

421
00:32:27,645 --> 00:32:29,044
Downlink.

422
00:32:29,147 --> 00:32:30,671
Thank God.

423
00:32:31,349 --> 00:32:33,408
<i>- Yeah.
- Hey, Jack. How's it hanging?</i>

424
00:32:33,518 --> 00:32:35,145
Fair to middling. How about you?

425
00:32:35,253 --> 00:32:37,881
I'm doing just fine, thanks for asking.
Here's the deal.

426
00:32:37,989 --> 00:32:41,686
I'm going to shoot me one of these kids
every hour till the chopper gets here.

427
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:45,229
That's one an hour, every hour,
starting at 4:00 p. m.

428
00:32:45,697 --> 00:32:48,393
And I'm also gonna need me
100 rounds of ammo...

429
00:32:48,499 --> 00:32:49,761
<i>for the Glocks as well.</i>

430
00:32:49,867 --> 00:32:52,961
Why, I guess you're not hearing me, Ted.
No ammo, period.

431
00:32:53,237 --> 00:32:56,866
The food will be there in 40 minutes.
When you get it, I get the girl.

432
00:32:56,975 --> 00:33:01,412
You owe me this one.
You shot one. This one's mine.

433
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:06,482
- You really want her, Jack?
- I really want them all, Ted.

434
00:33:07,385 --> 00:33:10,650
You're a pistol, that's what you are, Jack.
You're one big pistol.

435
00:33:10,755 --> 00:33:14,156
All right, I'm going to let you
have this little yellow hacker.

436
00:33:14,258 --> 00:33:17,557
For the food
and for that chopper at 4:00 p. m.

437
00:33:23,868 --> 00:33:28,168
That's good, Mr. Potter, that's real good.
We can get your helo in 30 minutes.

438
00:33:28,506 --> 00:33:31,907
We don't need one, Lenny.
We're not letting him go mobile.

439
00:33:32,010 --> 00:33:34,570
- He's going to kill them all.
- So he says.

440
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:36,374
And you're willing to take that risk?

441
00:33:36,481 --> 00:33:40,474
That's my job, Lenny.
That's why I'm here, to talk him out of it.

442
00:33:56,267 --> 00:33:58,394
- Will you even talk to us?
- I have no comment.

443
00:33:58,503 --> 00:34:00,596
Are you here to take over
the hostage negotiation?

444
00:34:00,705 --> 00:34:02,798
I've nothing to say,
I'm not here to take over.

445
00:34:02,907 --> 00:34:06,104
- Is the governor trying to get Potter fired?
- No, it's nothing like that.

446
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:09,702
We are doing the best we can,
we're trying very hard.

447
00:34:09,814 --> 00:34:11,179
We're being held a mile...

448
00:34:19,791 --> 00:34:20,985
Move it!

449
00:34:21,559 --> 00:34:23,220
- Let's go!
- Come on.

450
00:34:34,305 --> 00:34:37,638
Our state police HRT is here,
along with the brass.

451
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:42,035
- Did you request them?
- No, I did not. I would have told you if I did.

452
00:34:46,918 --> 00:34:48,385
Agent Potter.

453
00:34:51,789 --> 00:34:55,190
I'm Roland Marks, Assistant Attorney
General for the state of New York.

454
00:34:56,994 --> 00:34:59,724
And this is State Police Major Tremain.

455
00:35:00,231 --> 00:35:02,699
I brought our hostage rescue team
with me, Mr. Potter.

456
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,461
They would have been here hours ago...

457
00:35:04,569 --> 00:35:08,005
but, if you can believe it,
we never received any kind of notification...

458
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:09,733
or request for assistance.

459
00:35:10,241 --> 00:35:14,007
The governor thought I should get
down here and offer our assistance...

460
00:35:14,112 --> 00:35:17,377
make sure there are no more
communication glitches like that one.

461
00:35:17,482 --> 00:35:20,940
Thank you, but that was no glitch,
we have the situation under control.

462
00:35:21,052 --> 00:35:23,179
But the FBI HRT is in Miami.

463
00:35:23,287 --> 00:35:26,518
I know for a fact they can't leave
before tonight, at the earliest.

464
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:29,092
- That's true.
- He shot a hostage.

465
00:35:29,293 --> 00:35:31,090
If he shoots one, he'll shoot the others.

466
00:35:31,195 --> 00:35:35,154
That calls for an immediate tactical
response, it's standard operating procedure.

467
00:35:35,266 --> 00:35:37,234
That's not my judgment in this case.

468
00:35:39,170 --> 00:35:43,231
- I notice that you're monitoring the press.
- Yes.

469
00:35:44,775 --> 00:35:47,642
Do you realize that there's
a great deal of public interest...

470
00:35:47,745 --> 00:35:50,441
- and sympathy for the deaf children?
- I bet there is.

471
00:35:50,548 --> 00:35:53,176
Yet, you've ignored
every request for a press briefing.

472
00:35:53,284 --> 00:35:55,343
Yes, we're very busy here.

473
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:58,618
In fact, if that's all, we're still busy.

474
00:35:59,891 --> 00:36:02,519
What? Are you telling us to leave?

475
00:36:03,161 --> 00:36:06,562
As you can see, sir, this is
a very small space for us all to work in.

476
00:36:07,598 --> 00:36:10,658
- Can I see you outside?
- Certainly.

477
00:36:13,738 --> 00:36:15,797
Are you aware that everything
in that shack...

478
00:36:15,907 --> 00:36:18,273
and the people are working
for the state of New York?

479
00:36:18,376 --> 00:36:22,142
And we appreciate the assistance,
but this is still a Federal operation.

480
00:36:22,246 --> 00:36:25,079
- You're not planning an assault, are you?
- No.

481
00:36:25,183 --> 00:36:28,846
Have you offered to exchange yourself
or other personnel for those children?

482
00:36:28,953 --> 00:36:31,319
- Have you asked for volunteers?
- No.

483
00:36:31,422 --> 00:36:34,653
We understand they've offered to trade
the hostages for a helicopter.

484
00:36:34,759 --> 00:36:37,125
- They're not getting one.
- Well, why not?

485
00:36:37,228 --> 00:36:40,686
You could track it on radar with
a homing device, they wouldn't get away.

486
00:36:40,798 --> 00:36:42,129
It's too risky.

487
00:36:42,233 --> 00:36:44,929
There is a known quantity of casualties
right now.

488
00:36:45,503 --> 00:36:47,471
You just came off a suspension, didn't you?

489
00:36:47,572 --> 00:36:50,166
No, I took leave for personal reasons.

490
00:36:51,809 --> 00:36:54,801
Everyone has the greatest sympathy
about Mrs. Potter.

491
00:36:54,912 --> 00:36:58,177
- Including, clearly, the congressmen who...
- Look, I don't know you...

492
00:36:58,282 --> 00:37:00,978
so don't go mentioning
sympathy for my wife.

493
00:37:01,285 --> 00:37:04,846
You're free to complain about me
to the governor or to Washington...

494
00:37:04,956 --> 00:37:07,948
you be my guest. Excuse me.

495
00:37:11,796 --> 00:37:13,127
You got it?

496
00:37:19,937 --> 00:37:21,404
Light him up.

497
00:37:23,341 --> 00:37:27,175
<i>- Lower your face shield and say something.
- What should I say?</i>

498
00:37:27,445 --> 00:37:29,743
That's fine. Okay, get him dressed.

499
00:37:31,916 --> 00:37:35,352
Get as close to the doorway as you can,
I want to see what's inside.

500
00:37:35,453 --> 00:37:38,945
What kind of weapons they have,
radios, portable TVs, whatever.

501
00:37:39,056 --> 00:37:40,648
Yes, sir. No problem.

502
00:37:40,758 --> 00:37:42,783
You should stand in the doorway...

503
00:37:42,893 --> 00:37:45,885
but do not, under any circumstances,
go inside.

504
00:37:46,230 --> 00:37:48,824
All right, but what if he won't release
her unless I do?

505
00:37:48,933 --> 00:37:50,924
You just leave the food, walk away.

506
00:37:51,035 --> 00:37:54,471
If it's between you and the hostage,
you save yourself first.

507
00:37:54,572 --> 00:37:57,473
- Well, sir, if I...
- That's an order, trooper.

508
00:37:58,309 --> 00:38:01,005
Okay, send him out.
I'll tell him you're coming.

509
00:38:09,053 --> 00:38:12,022
- Hey, Sonny.
- Yeah.

510
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:15,752
Sonny, bring down that teacher
and that little kid...

511
00:38:15,860 --> 00:38:18,829
who makes all of them hacking noises,
bring them down right now.

512
00:38:18,929 --> 00:38:20,294
Just a second.

513
00:38:22,733 --> 00:38:24,166
Hey, Jack...

514
00:38:24,268 --> 00:38:26,293
<i>I'm sure you got a wire on that boy, right?</i>

515
00:38:26,404 --> 00:38:29,567
- What if I do?
- I want you to tell him to stop, right now.

516
00:38:29,674 --> 00:38:30,641
Why?

517
00:38:30,741 --> 00:38:33,437
I don't want him to get here
and think he can snoop around.

518
00:38:33,544 --> 00:38:36,445
I know how you fuckers work,
I've been barricaded before, man.

519
00:38:36,547 --> 00:38:39,675
- I'm a pro.
- Stevie, hold it right there.

520
00:38:56,834 --> 00:38:58,426
Bring them here.

521
00:39:05,476 --> 00:39:07,842
Okay, we've got some food coming.

522
00:39:07,945 --> 00:39:10,880
Some food that's outside.

523
00:39:11,148 --> 00:39:14,914
You are going to go outside
and get the food...

524
00:39:18,422 --> 00:39:21,084
You're gonna go home, okay?

525
00:39:21,192 --> 00:39:23,023
So, that's the deal. Go get food...

526
00:39:26,397 --> 00:39:28,331
I'm just going to have to shoot her.

527
00:39:32,570 --> 00:39:36,506
Go. Come on, we're hungry. Let's move it.

528
00:39:36,741 --> 00:39:38,003
That'll do it.

529
00:39:39,744 --> 00:39:41,541
Come on, all the way.

530
00:39:44,782 --> 00:39:47,546
When you come back, I'll be waiting for you.

531
00:39:55,326 --> 00:39:57,226
Yeah, love, go.

532
00:40:06,670 --> 00:40:07,762
Shit.

533
00:40:09,073 --> 00:40:10,506
Get him back.

534
00:40:15,913 --> 00:40:17,278
Uplink.

535
00:40:18,449 --> 00:40:23,079
Hey, Ted, I'm coming out there.
That kid forgot two large pepperonis.

536
00:40:40,337 --> 00:40:41,304
Downlink.

537
00:40:42,873 --> 00:40:45,933
- Yeah.
- I want you to stop right where you are.

538
00:40:46,043 --> 00:40:48,841
And I want you to tell that cop-boy of yours
to go back to you...

539
00:40:48,946 --> 00:40:52,109
'cause I don't want you getting closer to her
than you already are.

540
00:40:52,216 --> 00:40:53,706
Stevie, come here.

541
00:40:58,522 --> 00:40:59,580
Melanie...

542
00:41:00,491 --> 00:41:03,187
I'm John Potter, I'm with the FBI.

543
00:41:03,394 --> 00:41:05,021
Can you understand me?

544
00:41:05,663 --> 00:41:08,154
Good. I want you to pretend...

545
00:41:08,399 --> 00:41:12,836
that you're looking through the pizza boxes,
but keep your eyes on me.

546
00:41:14,572 --> 00:41:17,268
- Move over there, closer, and go slow.
- Yes, sir.

547
00:41:17,808 --> 00:41:20,038
Don't block her line of vision to me.

548
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:22,446
Melanie.

549
00:41:27,184 --> 00:41:30,449
...but we can see you signing
through the upstairs window.

550
00:41:31,388 --> 00:41:35,347
We're trying to get you out,
but we need your help, okay?

551
00:41:36,927 --> 00:41:41,421
I want to know how the children are.
And I want to know about the three men.

552
00:41:44,101 --> 00:41:47,832
- Just hurry this shit up, Jack.
- Yeah, okay.

553
00:41:48,506 --> 00:41:50,303
Little faster, Stevie.

554
00:41:51,275 --> 00:41:52,242
Good.

555
00:41:52,710 --> 00:41:55,611
I want you to take the pizza and go back.

556
00:41:55,980 --> 00:41:58,039
I'm sorry I have to send you back.

557
00:41:59,383 --> 00:42:00,907
You be careful.

558
00:42:02,319 --> 00:42:04,116
Be careful.

559
00:42:16,333 --> 00:42:17,698
<i>- Yes.
- Ted.</i>

560
00:42:18,435 --> 00:42:20,767
You got your pizza, send out Beverly.

561
00:42:20,871 --> 00:42:22,668
You're sure that's the one you want, Jack?

562
00:42:22,773 --> 00:42:24,434
You sure you don't want Melanie instead?

563
00:42:24,542 --> 00:42:27,204
I can sort of see you looking
at her out there.

564
00:42:27,311 --> 00:42:29,677
She does have a set on her, doesn't she?

565
00:42:30,347 --> 00:42:33,441
- Send the girl out, Ted.
- Okay.

566
00:42:35,119 --> 00:42:39,283
Bye-bye. Get rid of this kid.

567
00:42:42,226 --> 00:42:43,989
Go get her.

568
00:42:53,971 --> 00:42:54,938
Okay.

569
00:43:16,193 --> 00:43:17,285
What is it?

570
00:43:17,394 --> 00:43:19,919
Chief Stillwell saw someone
at the south end of the field.

571
00:43:20,030 --> 00:43:22,225
- Did he fire?
- No, shot came from the building.

572
00:43:22,333 --> 00:43:23,732
Sir, look.

573
00:43:26,303 --> 00:43:27,395
Shit!

574
00:43:28,305 --> 00:43:30,933
- Tell everybody, no return fire.
- Yes, sir.

575
00:43:31,508 --> 00:43:34,875
- I'm coming up. Stevie, come with me.
- Yes, sir.

576
00:43:38,248 --> 00:43:41,740
Theodore Handy, I'm Roland Marks!

577
00:43:42,319 --> 00:43:45,254
Assistant Attorney General
for the state of New York.

578
00:43:47,758 --> 00:43:50,989
I want you to let the kids go
and take me in their place.

579
00:43:51,128 --> 00:43:53,153
We don't want you.

580
00:43:57,201 --> 00:43:59,999
Handy, I'm alone and unarmed.

581
00:44:01,705 --> 00:44:02,865
He's stepping lively.

582
00:44:02,973 --> 00:44:05,407
If he gets any closer,
I'm gonna have to shoot him.

583
00:44:08,879 --> 00:44:12,007
For the love of God, Handy,
let those children go.

584
00:44:16,453 --> 00:44:19,149
<i>Marks, this is Potter.</i>

585
00:44:19,556 --> 00:44:22,616
<i>Get under cover immediately,
or you will be arrested.</i>

586
00:44:22,893 --> 00:44:24,554
I'm trying to save them.

587
00:44:24,995 --> 00:44:27,190
<i>No, you are endangering them.</i>

588
00:44:28,465 --> 00:44:32,663
I want you to give up the kids, Handy,
and take me in their place.

589
00:44:32,870 --> 00:44:34,235
Do you hear me?

590
00:44:34,938 --> 00:44:38,305
I said I don't want you.

591
00:44:43,113 --> 00:44:46,742
I swear, that one went right by his ear.

592
00:44:46,850 --> 00:44:48,784
There's no reason to shoot me. I'm unarmed.

593
00:44:48,886 --> 00:44:50,615
Kissing the worms, man.

594
00:44:50,721 --> 00:44:52,450
- I just want to talk to you.
- Hey.

595
00:44:52,556 --> 00:44:54,183
Hey, Sonny.

596
00:44:54,291 --> 00:44:56,418
- Yeah.
- Get your ass down here, right now.

597
00:44:56,527 --> 00:44:58,927
What you doing, girl?
You snooping around here?

598
00:44:59,029 --> 00:45:00,018
What?

599
00:45:00,130 --> 00:45:02,564
Get your ass down here
and get this lady upstairs.

600
00:45:02,666 --> 00:45:03,792
Get her now.

601
00:45:04,101 --> 00:45:06,069
We have to get him out of there.

602
00:45:06,370 --> 00:45:07,803
Stay low, son.

603
00:45:11,542 --> 00:45:14,067
I'm trying to help you, you understand that?

604
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:18,542
Get down on the ground, sir.
You're interfering with a Federal operation.

605
00:45:19,116 --> 00:45:21,949
What the hell are you talking about?
You're working for me.

606
00:45:22,052 --> 00:45:23,713
And don't you forget it.

607
00:45:26,156 --> 00:45:27,123
Handy...

608
00:45:28,325 --> 00:45:30,293
if you let the kids come out...

609
00:45:30,961 --> 00:45:33,691
I'm prepared to negotiate in good faith.

610
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:39,727
- I'm gonna have to take you in, sir.
- Yeah, I'd like to see you try.

611
00:45:39,837 --> 00:45:43,170
Sir, my orders are to shoot you in the leg
and drag you back.

612
00:45:50,547 --> 00:45:51,536
Let's go!

613
00:45:58,388 --> 00:46:01,221
<i>Handy, you son of a bitch,
I'll see you rot in hell.</i>

614
00:46:04,161 --> 00:46:05,719
Crazy old fuck.

615
00:46:06,997 --> 00:46:08,055
Let's eat.

616
00:46:15,139 --> 00:46:17,107
Never exchange hostages, Marks.

617
00:46:17,207 --> 00:46:19,607
The whole point of negotiation
is to devalue them.

618
00:46:19,710 --> 00:46:22,304
If he'd gotten you,
it would have made my job impossible.

619
00:46:22,412 --> 00:46:23,401
I don't see why.

620
00:46:23,514 --> 00:46:26,142
A hostage like you would have boosted
his sense of power...

621
00:46:26,250 --> 00:46:27,342
and courage a hundred times.

622
00:46:27,451 --> 00:46:29,510
He'd up his demands and stick to them.

623
00:46:29,620 --> 00:46:32,384
I don't care about that.
What I care about is those hostages.

624
00:46:32,489 --> 00:46:35,390
Really? It had nothing to do with
those cameras out there?

625
00:46:35,492 --> 00:46:38,655
Are you implying that I'd risk my life
for some kind of publicity?

626
00:46:38,762 --> 00:46:41,595
Unlike you, I happen to care about
those women and children.

627
00:46:41,698 --> 00:46:44,098
Unlike you,
I'm willing to risk my life for them.

628
00:46:44,201 --> 00:46:47,398
I'm not the one concerned
with rebuilding a shattered reputation.

629
00:46:47,504 --> 00:46:48,471
John.

630
00:46:49,573 --> 00:46:50,665
Yeah, what's up?

631
00:46:50,774 --> 00:46:54,369
There's a detective second
on the Pittsburgh PD, a Sharon Foster.

632
00:46:54,745 --> 00:46:57,714
She negotiated Handy's surrender
in the holdup five years ago.

633
00:46:57,815 --> 00:47:00,682
- He gave up to her?
- He did, yes. Appears she's pretty good.

634
00:47:00,784 --> 00:47:03,719
- Then get her up here.
- I thought you might say that.

635
00:47:03,821 --> 00:47:07,279
So I connected her through
to the 5:00 puddle jumper from Buffalo.

636
00:47:07,391 --> 00:47:09,689
The only reason
you needed to tell me that now...

637
00:47:09,793 --> 00:47:13,058
- was to give me time to rein my temper.
- You know me so well.

638
00:47:13,197 --> 00:47:14,164
Thanks.

639
00:47:17,534 --> 00:47:20,196
Let's get something straight, Marks,
and you, too, Major.

640
00:47:20,304 --> 00:47:22,795
If either of you
interfere with this barricade again...

641
00:47:22,906 --> 00:47:26,307
I will arrest you and I'll see the US Attorney
makes sure you do time.

642
00:47:26,410 --> 00:47:28,275
Then you should consider
your own actions...

643
00:47:28,378 --> 00:47:31,541
because you could be facing state charges
for reckless endangerment.

644
00:47:31,648 --> 00:47:33,616
I'll try to live with that.

645
00:47:36,820 --> 00:47:39,414
Potter's bluffing. He'd never make that stick.

646
00:47:39,523 --> 00:47:41,457
Yeah, you wanna take the chance?

647
00:47:41,558 --> 00:47:43,958
So we just stand here
and watch them be murdered...

648
00:47:44,061 --> 00:47:46,291
not lift a finger? Is that it?

649
00:47:46,763 --> 00:47:47,821
No.

650
00:47:47,931 --> 00:47:51,389
What we do is, hope to God
that Potter knows what he's doing.

651
00:47:51,501 --> 00:47:52,559
Excuse me.

652
00:48:20,364 --> 00:48:21,331
How is she?

653
00:48:21,431 --> 00:48:24,025
They had to give her a shot,
but she should be all right.

654
00:48:24,134 --> 00:48:27,399
- When will we be able to question her?
- She's at the window.

655
00:48:31,775 --> 00:48:33,299
The children are okay.

656
00:48:33,911 --> 00:48:36,141
They're scared, but they're all right.

657
00:48:38,248 --> 00:48:40,944
They took Susan downstairs
and tied her up...

658
00:48:41,385 --> 00:48:44,013
with the young one, right below us.

659
00:48:44,221 --> 00:48:47,486
- The rapist.
- Supposedly likes very young children.

660
00:48:47,591 --> 00:48:49,559
Susan might be too old for him.

661
00:48:51,094 --> 00:48:55,724
They have a gun. Two shotguns and tools.

662
00:48:58,669 --> 00:48:59,761
New ones...

663
00:49:00,804 --> 00:49:04,865
a hammer and a big monkey wrench.

664
00:49:05,909 --> 00:49:08,036
I think I've found a way to escape.

665
00:49:08,345 --> 00:49:11,746
There's a broken-down staircase
that they're not guarding.

666
00:49:12,449 --> 00:49:15,475
I know you can't answer me,
or tell me what to do...

667
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:18,179
but I think you would want me to do it.

668
00:49:18,689 --> 00:49:20,350
I don't want you to do it.

669
00:49:22,125 --> 00:49:23,752
And so I will try.

670
00:49:31,101 --> 00:49:33,001
You like some pizza?

671
00:49:34,638 --> 00:49:37,129
No? Why?

672
00:49:37,741 --> 00:49:39,834
You must be hungry.

673
00:49:39,943 --> 00:49:42,912
Have some. Look.

674
00:49:45,482 --> 00:49:46,574
Good pizza.

675
00:49:47,284 --> 00:49:50,412
I haven't had pizza
in about eight-and-a-half months.

676
00:50:36,199 --> 00:50:37,257
Want some?

677
00:50:38,702 --> 00:50:39,669
Yeah.

678
00:50:40,804 --> 00:50:43,773
There you go.

679
00:50:46,743 --> 00:50:47,801
Good, huh?

680
00:51:03,160 --> 00:51:04,627
It's good stuff.

681
00:51:27,551 --> 00:51:28,518
Downlink.

682
00:51:32,589 --> 00:51:35,217
- Yeah, hello, Ted.
- You know, Jack...

683
00:51:35,692 --> 00:51:39,321
it's damn near 4:00 p. m.,
and I haven't heard nor seen no helicopter.

684
00:51:40,263 --> 00:51:43,426
You gotta give us some time.
We're having trouble with the bulldozer.

685
00:51:43,533 --> 00:51:44,761
What bulldozer?

686
00:51:45,635 --> 00:51:48,103
Who the fuck asked for a bulldozer?

687
00:51:48,205 --> 00:51:51,538
<i>Come on, Ted, we're both looking out
at the same field.</i>

688
00:51:51,675 --> 00:51:53,905
Where's the helicopter supposed to land?

689
00:51:54,010 --> 00:51:56,274
All that old junk, those old fence posts...

690
00:51:56,379 --> 00:51:58,574
we gotta clear an area for 100 feet around.

691
00:51:58,682 --> 00:52:01,173
I know you want the helicopter
close to the building.

692
00:52:01,284 --> 00:52:02,717
<i>You're damn right I do.</i>

693
00:52:02,819 --> 00:52:03,786
You see?

694
00:52:05,489 --> 00:52:09,118
<i>- What about a pontoon chopper?
- A pontoon chopper.</i>

695
00:52:09,226 --> 00:52:13,060
<i>- I'd have never thought about that.
- You damn well should've thought about it.</i>

696
00:52:13,163 --> 00:52:15,859
<i>There's a goddamn river
out back here behind the building.</i>

697
00:52:15,966 --> 00:52:19,993
<i>- Why, yes, but that's the Niagara River.
- Yeah, I know it's the Niagara River, Jack.</i>

698
00:52:20,103 --> 00:52:23,402
<i>Good for you.
Because I had no idea till I got here.</i>

